\pard\f0\fs28   {\b G. parnassica} Halácsy, {\i  Magyar Bot. Lapok}{\b  11}: 136 (1912), from S.C. Greece (Parnassos), and possibly also Samothraki, is perhaps conspecific with {\b 20}. It has the leaves silvery-sericeous on both surfaces and the standard 9-13 mm, densely sericeous.
